WEBVTT

00:00.667 --> 00:04.136
♪

00:04.138 --> 00:06.105
Spike: Starlight Glimmer?

00:06.107 --> 00:08.107
I was sure I saw her, Spike.

00:08.109 --> 00:11.210
Welcome home, Twilight!

00:11.212 --> 00:14.179
We travelled back in time to
when Rainbow Dash performed

00:14.181 --> 00:17.683
her first Sonic Rainboom?

00:17.685 --> 00:20.586
Without the Rainboom,
you and your friends

00:20.588 --> 00:24.323
will never form your
special cutie mark bond.

00:24.325 --> 00:28.594
But whatever Starlight did in
the past changed things here.

00:28.596 --> 00:31.563
I don't want to live in
that awful future we saw.

00:31.565 --> 00:33.365
I don't think
you'll have to.

00:33.367 --> 00:36.435
All servants of Queen
Chrysalis found in these woods

00:36.437 --> 00:39.505
must be destroyed!

00:41.641 --> 00:45.277
<i>♪ My little pony,</i>
<i>my little pony ♪</i>

00:45.279 --> 00:47.212
<i>♪ Aaaahhh </i>

00:47.214 --> 00:49.148
<i>♪ My little Pony </i>

00:49.150 --> 00:51.650
<i>♪ I used to wonder what</i>
<i>friendship could be. ♪</i>

00:51.652 --> 00:53.419
<i>♪ My Little Pony </i>

00:53.421 --> 00:56.088
<i>♪ Until you all shared</i>
<i>its magic with me. ♪</i>

00:56.090 --> 00:58.090
<i>♪ Big adventure! </i>
<i>♪ Tons of fun </i>

00:58.092 --> 01:00.259
<i>♪ A beautiful heart!  ♪</i>
<i>Faithful and strong! ♪</i>

01:00.261 --> 01:02.428
<i>♪ Sharing kindness </i>
<i>♪ it's an easy feat </i>

01:02.430 --> 01:04.496
<i>♪ And magic makes it</i>
<i>all complete! ♪</i>

01:04.498 --> 01:06.532
<i>♪ To have my little pony </i>

01:06.534 --> 01:10.202
<i>♪ Do you know you're all</i>
<i>my very best friends? ♪</i>

01:10.204 --> 01:12.604
♪

01:18.311 --> 01:23.115
Wait! We're not changelings!
I'm a pony! And he's a dragon!

01:23.117 --> 01:25.184
A likely story!

01:25.186 --> 01:27.386
Do something dragonish!

01:27.388 --> 01:29.121
[whoosh]

01:29.123 --> 01:29.822
[cough]

01:29.824 --> 01:31.390
That works.

01:31.392 --> 01:33.325
The servants of Chrysalis
will do anything

01:33.327 --> 01:35.694
to save their evil skins!

01:35.696 --> 01:36.762
Zecora: STOP!

01:38.364 --> 01:39.431
If they are
changelings,

01:39.433 --> 01:41.633
we'll soon see.

01:41.635 --> 01:45.404
Though I think they're not
what they appear to be.

01:45.406 --> 01:47.773
Zecora! Please,
you have to listen.

01:51.344 --> 01:54.613
Beneath this salve
no changeling hides,

01:54.615 --> 01:57.349
for it reveals the
truth inside.

01:57.351 --> 02:02.688
♪

02:02.690 --> 02:05.624
[gasps]

02:05.626 --> 02:07.493
What does it mean?

02:07.495 --> 02:09.728
The meaning is far worse, I see.

02:09.730 --> 02:13.265
For it is we who should not be.

02:13.267 --> 02:15.134
I think I can explain.

02:15.136 --> 02:18.570
I'm sure you can, but
let's not talk here.

02:18.572 --> 02:21.607
Chrysalis and her army
will soon draw near.

02:27.247 --> 02:29.781
The changelings took
over not long ago,

02:29.783 --> 02:33.452
though I'll wager in
your world that isn't so.

02:33.454 --> 02:36.255
Chrysalis and her army tried
to take over Canterlot,

02:36.257 --> 02:38.290
but my friends
and I stopped her.

02:38.292 --> 02:41.593
Those friends as you know
them are not here, alas.

02:41.595 --> 02:45.297
But tell me how all
this came to pass.

02:45.299 --> 02:48.233
Starlight Glimmer. A pony
who traveled back in time

02:48.235 --> 02:50.936
to stop my friends and me
from ever coming together.

02:50.938 --> 02:53.438
And it is these friends
you have in life,

02:53.440 --> 02:55.941
that keep Equestria
free from strife?

02:55.943 --> 02:58.710
I guess so. But this is the
second time I've come back

02:58.712 --> 03:01.446
and this world is even
worse than the last one.

03:01.448 --> 03:03.949
If Starlight keeps doing
the same thing in the past,

03:03.951 --> 03:06.485
how could the present
be so different?

03:06.487 --> 03:12.858
Ahhh, time is a river where even
the tiniest changes seen...

03:12.860 --> 03:16.862
Can lead to a cascade
of effects downstream.

03:16.864 --> 03:21.867
♪

03:21.869 --> 03:24.503
This part of the forest
is dark and damp,

03:24.505 --> 03:26.838
but it's done well
to hide our camp.

03:36.416 --> 03:37.583
This is cozy.

03:37.585 --> 03:39.551
[scream]

03:39.553 --> 03:42.487
Please, you have to help us!

03:42.489 --> 03:44.489
The changelings
attacked Ponyville.

03:44.491 --> 03:47.459
We barely escaped
with our lives!

03:47.461 --> 03:50.229
The only changeling
attack I see

03:50.231 --> 03:53.498
is the one that come
here looking for me.

03:53.500 --> 03:57.302
It's taken quite a while
to find you, Zecora.

03:57.304 --> 03:58.971
[laughs]

03:58.973 --> 04:00.806
[whoosh]

04:00.808 --> 04:07.379
<i>♪ [dramatic] </i>

04:07.381 --> 04:10.882
[evil laugh]

04:10.884 --> 04:13.552
What a lovely
village you've chosen

04:13.554 --> 04:16.989
to stage your little resistance.

04:16.991 --> 04:19.925
It looks absolutely
delicious!

04:22.929 --> 04:26.632
Oh, come now, Zecora,
you're vastly outnumbered.

04:26.634 --> 04:33.672
♪

04:36.276 --> 04:38.777
I know you don't want
your charges hurt.

04:38.779 --> 04:41.713
Come quietly to the
dungeons of Canterlot

04:41.715 --> 04:44.683
and I promise to leave
the others alone.

04:44.685 --> 04:46.985
Why would she ever trust you!

04:46.987 --> 04:49.521
Even if there's a chance
Chrysalis will honor her word,

04:49.523 --> 04:52.924
Race to the map while we
hold off their attack.

04:52.926 --> 04:55.527
Stop Starlight and put the
whole world back on track.

04:57.063 --> 05:00.299
Time to make a decision, Zecora.

05:00.301 --> 05:02.334
Even if what you are
saying were true,

05:02.336 --> 05:04.836
we'd never surrender
to a creature like you.

05:04.838 --> 05:07.539
[war cries]

05:07.541 --> 05:09.708
♪

05:09.710 --> 05:12.911
[crashing]

05:12.913 --> 05:14.513
♪

05:14.515 --> 05:16.315
[panting]

05:16.317 --> 05:23.355
♪

05:25.992 --> 05:28.627
[whoosh]

05:37.804 --> 05:41.907
Not bad. But it's going to
take a lot more than that!

05:41.909 --> 05:44.743
Lucky for you, there's
more where that came from!

05:57.023 --> 05:59.424
You've really got
to work on your aim!

05:59.426 --> 06:06.365
♪

06:06.966 --> 06:10.502
[panting]

06:10.504 --> 06:11.737
WHOA!

06:14.073 --> 06:16.708
What are you doing? You
have to finish your race!

06:16.710 --> 06:19.911
No way! This is
way more exciting.

06:19.913 --> 06:23.582
See? You can't stop me
no matter what you do.

06:23.584 --> 06:25.884
[whoosh]

06:25.886 --> 06:27.052
Aw, man!

06:28.621 --> 06:30.155
[grunts]

06:30.157 --> 06:32.858
[groan]

06:32.860 --> 06:34.693
That's strange.

06:34.695 --> 06:36.862
Well, you obviously
don't mean us failing,

06:36.864 --> 06:39.097
because that's becoming
pretty routine.

06:39.099 --> 06:41.533
No. It's just the other
times we've come back,

06:41.535 --> 06:43.602
it's been day, but look.

06:45.171 --> 06:47.005
Why would the map
would bring us back

06:47.007 --> 06:49.174
to a different time of
day than when we left?

06:49.176 --> 06:51.543
Um, maybe we should
figure it out later.

06:52.945 --> 06:55.447
[growls]

07:01.154 --> 07:02.754
[panicked shouts]

07:02.756 --> 07:04.089
[howling]

07:04.091 --> 07:06.124
[panting]

07:11.764 --> 07:14.966
The Castle of the Two Sisters!

07:14.968 --> 07:16.568
[howling]

07:16.570 --> 07:17.869
Well, don't just stand here!

07:21.040 --> 07:23.141
[slam]

07:23.143 --> 07:30.115
<i>♪ [mysterious music] </i>

07:31.884 --> 07:34.052
This place looks a lot
cleaner than I remember.

07:36.456 --> 07:38.824
Rarity?

07:38.826 --> 07:41.092
The castle isn't open
for viewings today.

07:41.094 --> 07:44.029
The tapestries all need
changing... again.

07:44.031 --> 07:45.964
Rarity, it's me.

07:45.966 --> 07:50.635
I don't socialize with dragons.
I don't know anypony who would.

07:50.637 --> 07:53.138
Rarity, you have
to listen to me.

07:53.140 --> 07:55.874
The future of
Equestria is at stake.

07:55.876 --> 07:58.143
I don't know how
you know my name,

07:58.145 --> 08:00.512
but I am far too busy to
entertain some tourist's

08:00.514 --> 08:02.080
ridiculous fantasies.

08:02.082 --> 08:04.950
I have to get back to the
map so I can stop Starlight

08:04.952 --> 08:07.619
from changing the past because
every present I come to

08:07.621 --> 08:09.154
is worse than the last!

08:09.156 --> 08:11.656
Time travel, you say?

08:18.998 --> 08:22.534
Now that's something
I would like to see.

08:26.272 --> 08:33.144
[evil laughter]

08:33.146 --> 08:37.849
Tell me how you came by this
magic to travel through time.

08:37.851 --> 08:40.552
The Princess asked
you a question!

08:40.554 --> 08:42.754
And unless you want to
end up in the dungeon,

08:42.756 --> 08:45.757
you'll tell her what
she wants to know.

08:45.759 --> 08:49.528
No pony in my kingdom but
me should possess a magic

08:49.530 --> 08:52.264
powerful enough to change time.

08:52.266 --> 08:54.266
Your kingdom?

08:54.268 --> 08:56.101
Who else?

08:56.103 --> 08:58.603
Um, Celestia, of course.

09:01.307 --> 09:05.744
[laughter]

09:05.746 --> 09:10.048
My sister has been imprisoned
in the moon for years!

09:10.050 --> 09:12.951
But it is no less a fate
than she sentenced me to.

09:12.953 --> 09:17.022
Now. Reveal to me the
source of this time magic.

09:19.325 --> 09:20.325
All right.

09:20.327 --> 09:21.993
Twilight! No!

09:21.995 --> 09:24.629
We have no choice, Spike.

09:24.631 --> 09:25.897
I can take you to it,

09:25.899 --> 09:28.300
but you'll have to get
past the Timber Wolves.

09:28.302 --> 09:31.703
I am the ruler of
all of Equestria.

09:31.705 --> 09:35.240
Do you think I can't
deal with Timber Wolves?

09:35.242 --> 09:39.177
No. I know you can.

09:39.179 --> 09:44.883
And if you were thinking
of trying to escape...

09:44.885 --> 09:48.320
it would be very
unfortunate for your friend.

09:50.890 --> 09:53.625
[night insect noises]

09:53.627 --> 09:58.797
[bark and whine]

09:58.799 --> 10:00.165
How does it work?

10:00.167 --> 10:02.033
A pony from my time used a spell

10:02.035 --> 10:04.336
to travel back and
change the past.

10:04.338 --> 10:07.339
And now you will give
this spell to me.

10:07.341 --> 10:10.208
With it, I will ensure that
the Elements of Harmony

10:10.210 --> 10:14.079
are never found and
my rein lasts forever!

10:14.081 --> 10:15.313
But it won't.

10:15.315 --> 10:19.618
In my world, my friends
and I found the elements

10:19.620 --> 10:21.286
and used them to defeat you.

10:21.288 --> 10:23.121
And I will do
everything in my power

10:23.123 --> 10:25.223
to bring that world back.

10:25.225 --> 10:26.358
NO!

10:26.360 --> 10:30.996
[whoosh]

10:30.998 --> 10:32.397
NOOOOOOO!

10:36.802 --> 10:40.372
Now more than ever, I know how
important it is to stop you.

10:42.174 --> 10:43.942
Well, good luck!

10:45.945 --> 10:47.646
[whoosh]

10:47.648 --> 10:48.780
Whoa!

10:50.383 --> 10:52.217
[power up]

10:52.219 --> 10:56.955
[rumbling]

11:01.260 --> 11:02.927
[zap]

11:06.365 --> 11:07.232
[squeak]

11:07.234 --> 11:12.937
♪

11:12.939 --> 11:14.706
[splattering]

11:14.708 --> 11:21.680
♪

11:22.848 --> 11:26.851
[engine hum]

11:26.853 --> 11:30.855
♪

11:30.857 --> 11:34.125
Up for another race-ending
fight, Twilight?

11:35.761 --> 11:38.863
No. You were right.
I can't stop you.

11:38.865 --> 11:40.265
[zap]

11:40.267 --> 11:42.467
But you can't stop
me from trying

11:42.469 --> 11:45.737
and we could be stuck doing
this for all eternity.

11:45.739 --> 11:48.073
If that's what it takes to
keep you and your friends

11:48.075 --> 11:51.710
from getting your cutie mark
connection, then I'm game.

11:51.712 --> 11:53.445
[zap]

11:53.447 --> 11:56.347
What you're doing goes
way beyond cutie marks.

11:56.349 --> 11:58.416
Everything we do
here in the past,

11:58.418 --> 12:00.185
even the smallest change,

12:00.187 --> 12:04.022
can snowball into an avalanche
of trouble for the future.

12:04.024 --> 12:06.324
Oh. Next I suppose
you'll tell me

12:06.326 --> 12:08.193
that the fate of
all of Equestria

12:08.195 --> 12:10.095
hangs in the balance.

12:10.097 --> 12:11.262
IT DOES!

12:11.264 --> 12:13.765
Spare me your over-blown ego.

12:13.767 --> 12:16.468
No group of friends, not
even Princess Twilight's,

12:16.470 --> 12:17.936
is that important.

12:17.938 --> 12:18.870
[zap]

12:18.872 --> 12:20.505
[screams]

12:20.507 --> 12:22.440
[whoosh]

12:22.442 --> 12:24.509
I don't know how important
other ponies' friendships are

12:24.511 --> 12:28.413
but I can show you what the
world is like without mine.

12:28.415 --> 12:34.753
[rushing wind]

12:41.427 --> 12:43.128
Where are we?

12:43.130 --> 12:46.998
The future. Or
rather, the present.

12:47.000 --> 12:48.967
But there's nothing here.

12:48.969 --> 12:51.169
I wish I could say
I was surprised.

12:51.171 --> 12:54.105
But every world I come back
to is worse than the last.

12:54.107 --> 12:56.441
I don't know why my friends
and I are so important

12:56.443 --> 12:59.911
to Equestria, but we are.

12:59.913 --> 13:01.813
I don't believe you!

13:01.815 --> 13:04.449
Come on, Starlight. Look around.

13:04.451 --> 13:07.886
Like I said, everything in
the past affects the future,

13:07.888 --> 13:12.924
even the tiniest act, and
what you're doing leads here.

13:12.926 --> 13:14.559
I know I can't stop you,

13:14.561 --> 13:17.328
but I thought showing you
this might change your mind.

13:17.330 --> 13:22.200
Change my mind? You don't
know anything about me.

13:22.202 --> 13:25.904
I was perfectly happy
before you and your friends

13:25.906 --> 13:27.906
ruined what I built.

13:27.908 --> 13:30.141
I don't know what happened
that led you to make

13:30.143 --> 13:32.076
your village
without cutie marks.

13:32.078 --> 13:35.280
And I'm sorry my friends
and I had to take it away.

13:35.282 --> 13:39.517
You want to know what happened
to me? I'll show you!

13:45.958 --> 13:49.260
[whoosh]

13:49.262 --> 13:54.399
That map of yours is connected
to every part of Equestria

13:54.401 --> 13:56.935
and this part is my home.

14:04.009 --> 14:06.411
Sunburst and I did
everything together.

14:06.413 --> 14:09.981
In fact, I don't remember
us ever being apart...

14:09.983 --> 14:11.382
until today.

14:16.288 --> 14:23.027
♪

14:28.968 --> 14:31.102
[zap]

14:31.104 --> 14:32.904
[whinny]

14:34.440 --> 14:40.612
[excited chatter]

14:40.614 --> 14:44.916
And just like that,
my friend was gone.

14:44.918 --> 14:47.218
His family recognized
his magical talent

14:47.220 --> 14:51.222
and sent him off to Canterlot.
I never saw him again.

14:51.224 --> 14:52.924
Why not?

14:52.926 --> 14:57.228
Because of his cutie mark!
He got his and I didn't.

14:57.230 --> 14:59.497
He moved on and I didn't.

14:59.499 --> 15:02.166
I stayed here and never
made another friend

15:02.168 --> 15:04.269
because I was too afraid
another cutie mark

15:04.271 --> 15:06.404
would take them away too!

15:06.406 --> 15:07.639
That's ridiculous.

15:07.641 --> 15:10.308
A cutie mark can't
take your friends away.

15:10.310 --> 15:12.911
Not everypony's lucky
enough to get her cutie mark

15:12.913 --> 15:14.479
at the same time as her friends.

15:18.484 --> 15:20.652
You don't know what it's
like to lose a friend

15:20.654 --> 15:22.387
because of a cutie mark.

15:22.389 --> 15:25.556
But once I stop the
Rainboom, you will!

15:27.293 --> 15:29.661
And when I destroy this scroll,

15:29.663 --> 15:32.330
there'll be no way
for you to change it!

15:32.332 --> 15:35.266
<i>♪ [intense orchestral] </i>

15:39.038 --> 15:40.471
Starlight, you're right.

15:40.473 --> 15:42.373
I don't know what
you went through,

15:42.375 --> 15:44.642
but I do know you
can't do this.

15:44.644 --> 15:47.679
I've seen where this
leads and so have you.

15:47.681 --> 15:49.547
I only saw what
you showed me.

15:49.549 --> 15:51.950
Who knows what'll
really happen?

15:51.952 --> 15:54.052
I've seen it a dozen times.

15:54.054 --> 15:55.653
Things don't turn out
well in an Equestria

15:55.655 --> 15:57.588
without my friends.

15:57.590 --> 16:01.125
Agh! What's so special
about your friends?

16:01.127 --> 16:03.728
How can a group of ponies
that are so different

16:03.730 --> 16:06.264
be so important?

16:06.266 --> 16:08.099
The differences between
me and my friends

16:08.101 --> 16:11.102
are the very things that
make our friendship strong.

16:11.104 --> 16:13.438
I thought Sunburst
and I were the same,

16:13.440 --> 16:15.106
but we turned out different

16:15.108 --> 16:17.608
and it tore our
friendship apart.

16:17.610 --> 16:20.445
So try again. Make new friends.

16:20.447 --> 16:22.380
And if something that
you can't control happens

16:22.382 --> 16:25.149
that changes things, work
through it together.

16:25.151 --> 16:27.452
That's what friendship is.

16:27.454 --> 16:29.654
And it's not just my
friendships that are important

16:29.656 --> 16:32.323
to Equestria. Everyponies' are.

16:32.325 --> 16:34.559
When yours ended,
it led us here,

16:34.561 --> 16:36.728
but just imagine all the
others that are out there

16:36.730 --> 16:39.330
waiting for you if you
just give them a chance.

16:39.332 --> 16:42.233
How do I know they won't
all end the same way?

16:42.235 --> 16:44.669
I guess it's up to you
to make sure they don't.

16:45.671 --> 16:47.105
[whoosh]

16:47.107 --> 16:54.145
♪

16:56.081 --> 16:57.482
[whoosh]

16:57.484 --> 17:04.355
♪

17:07.526 --> 17:14.032
♪

17:15.667 --> 17:19.037
[whoosh]

17:19.039 --> 17:20.805
♪

17:20.807 --> 17:24.742
One Castle of
Friendship. Check.

17:24.744 --> 17:27.779
What in Equestria was that?

17:27.781 --> 17:29.781
Is everypony OK?

17:29.783 --> 17:31.315
Can you do it again?

17:31.317 --> 17:34.419
One group of amazing
friends. Check.

17:34.421 --> 17:37.588
Yep, Spike. It looks
like we're home.

17:37.590 --> 17:41.626
Uh, what's she doing here?

17:41.628 --> 17:44.629
Actually, it's kind
of a long story.

17:50.836 --> 17:52.703
I mean, I knew my
Rainboom was awesome,

17:52.705 --> 17:55.640
but I never thought all of
Equestria depended on it.

17:55.642 --> 17:57.341
Or on us!

17:57.343 --> 17:58.676
I think it's more than that.

17:58.678 --> 18:00.778
Friendship connects
all of Equestria

18:00.780 --> 18:02.613
and undoing one group
of friends

18:02.615 --> 18:04.582
made its magic
less powerful.

18:04.584 --> 18:06.417
I can't believe y'all
were able to travel

18:06.419 --> 18:08.286
through time like that.

18:08.288 --> 18:11.656
That Starlight must
be pretty magical!

18:11.658 --> 18:13.691
She obviously has
more talent for magic

18:13.693 --> 18:16.094
than almost any pony I've seen.

18:16.096 --> 18:17.695
My magic couldn't stop her.

